WordPress is a free and open source content management system (CMS). Originally, 
its focus was on providing a platform for blogging, but throughout the last decade plus, 
it has become a general purpose CMS that can serve as a website builder.

1. Make sure it meets requierments
 - php --version
 - mysql --version
2. cd /var/www/html (navigate)
3. sudo wget https://wordpress.org/latest.tar.gz (download)
4. sudo tar -xzvf latest.tar.gz (extract)
5. Sudo su 
6. mysql -u root (login to mysql)
7. create user 'wordpress'@'localhost' identified by 'XXXXXXXXX'; (create a new user)
8. create database wordpress; (create database)
9. grant all privileges on wordpress.* to 'wordpress'@'localhost'; (allowing access)
10. show databases; (double checking)
12. cd /var/www/html/wordpress (navigating)
13.sudo cp wp-config-sample.php wp-config.php (coping)
14 sudo nano wp-config.php (editing login file)
